[Student "W"]
{The bidding has been as shown. The contract is 4\H 

Lead the \C8.

If partner had not doubled West's Stayman 2\C bid you would probably have started with one of your Jacks.

But partner <b>DID</b> double, and the double of a conventional bid clearly means that the doubler would like you to lead that suit.

 So lead a \C, and partner will take three \C tricks. With any other lead declarer would quickly discard a \C from dummy on a high \D, easily making the contract.

Declarer may still make the contract if he guesses the \HQ correctly, but maybe not.}
[Play "W"]C8

